Hey CG — enabled debug logging on the proxy and found the exact issue. The proxy is authenticating fine, but when it tries to log into Aurora as pgsi_ans00315015 using the password from Secrets Manager, Postgres rejects it because the user is IAM-only (no password set on the DB user itself).
Fix on your side: run
sqlALTER USER pgsi_ans00315015 WITH PASSWORD '<password stored in the secret>';
That way the user can be reached both by IAM (for pgAdmin) and by password (for the proxy). No changes on my side needed.
